 POLICE in Edinburgh have released CCTV footage of a man they want to trace after an indecent exposure . 
The incident happened at around 8.20pm on Saturday 16th May in the No 8 Lister Square bar in Edinburgh’s Quartermile development.
Police are keen to speak to the man pictured in relation to the ongoing enquiry and anyone who can assist in establishing his identity is asked to come forward.
He is described as white, around 6ft tall and between 60 and 70 years old. He is of medium to heavy build with grey hair in a side parting.
He was wearing a navy crew neck jumper, khaki green fleece and navy cords.
Detective Constable Johnson said: “This was a very distressing incident for the young woman in the bar and we are continuing with our enquiries.
“Anyone who can help us trace the male pictured within the CCTV footage is asked to contact police immediately.”
 Anyone with information can contact Police Scotland on 101 or contact Crimestoppers anonymously on 0800 555 111. 
